cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.GR 

The paper deals with image inpainting, specifically face completion, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) for semantic understanding and the introduction of a novel generative framework (collaGAN) suggest that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The tasks of landmark detection and semantic segmentation, which are collaboratively learned with face completion, indicate that the paper may also be relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories.
